items.title: India's Ports: Public-private partnership propelling growth
items.description: Public-Private Partnerships (PPPs) are transforming India's ports sector, facilitating substantial investments and improving efficiency. With the Landlord Port Model and strategic government initiatives, PPPs aim to enhance cargo handling capacity significantly, supporting India's vision of becoming a global manufacturing and export hub by 2047
